cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IT

The paper deals with an iterative learning approach for image reconstruction using deep neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach that relies on invertible networks, which falls under the category of generative models and could be classified as cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the memory requirements of the proposed approach, which could be categorized as cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also uses optimization techniques to train the model, which could be classified as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper proposes a new approach for solving inverse problems, which could be classified as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
